2.You are given two integer arrays nums1 and nums2 of sizes n and m, respectively. Calculate
the following values: answer1 : the number of indices i such that nums1[i] exists in nums2.
answer2 : the number of indices i such that nums2[i] exists in nums1 Return [answer1,answer2].

Code:
def findCounts(nums1, nums2):
    set1 = set(nums1)
    set2 = set(nums2)

    answer1 = sum(1 for x in nums1 if x in set2)
    answer2 = sum(1 for x in nums2 if x in set1)

    return [answer1, answer2]

