10.Given an array of integers nums, sort the array in ascending order and return it. You must
solve the problem without using any built-in functions in O(nlog(n)) time complexity and with the
smallest space complexity possible.

code:
def mergeSort(arr):
    if len(arr) <= 1:
        return arr

    mid = len(arr)//2
    left = mergeSort(arr[:mid])
    right = mergeSort(arr[mid:])

    return merge(left, right)

def merge(left, right):
    result = []
    i = j = 0

    while i < len(left) and j < len(right):
        if left[i] < right[j]:
            result.append(left[i])
            i += 1
        else:
            result.append(right[j])
            j += 1

    result.extend(left[i:])
    result.extend(right[j:])

    return result

# Example
print(mergeSort([5,2,3,1]))

output:
[1, 2, 3, 5]
